During a meeting in the Roosevelt Room, President Trump met with top executives from major car manufacturers to discuss environmental controls, fuel efficiency standards (CAFE standards), and increasing car manufacturing in the United States. The President emphasized the goal of having more cars made in the U.S. and exported overseas. The executives introduced themselves and their companies, and the President thanked Sergio Marchionne of Fiat Chrysler for moving operations from Mexico to Michigan. The President also expressed confidence in Administrator Pruitt of the EPA and stated that he is renegotiating the NAFTA trade deal, which he believes has been a "terrible disaster" for the United States. The President concluded the meeting by thanking everyone for attending.